<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <title>Project 1</title>
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

        <section class="container mt-4 pt-5" style="padding-top: 80px;">
            <h2 class="text-center">Music Library</h2>
            <p class="text-center">This project is a simple Music Library CRUD application built with Node.js, Express, and Bootstrap. It
                allows users to add, view, edit, and delete music entries, each containing a title, singer, description,
                image, and YouTube link.</p>
                <br>
            <img src="/images/musicApp.png" alt="My Photo" class="img-fluid d-block mx-auto my-3">

            <p>The app features full CRUD functionality, form handling, dynamic HTML generation, and a reusable
                Bootstrap navigation bar. Music data is stored in an in-memory array, and each entry includes a title,
                singer, description, image, and YouTube link. This project strengthened my understanding of server-side
                routing, form processing, and building simple web applications using Express.</p>
            <p>The Music Library app demonstrates the fundamentals of server-side development using Express.</p>
            <p>It includes:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>HTTP routing</li>
                <li>Dynamic HTML rendering</li>
                <li>Form handling</li>
                <li>Updating in-memory data</li>
                <li>Bootstrap</li>
                <li>RESTful style routes</li>
            </ul>
            <p>This app does not use a database. Instead, it stores data in a simple in-memory array for learning
                purposes.</p>

            <p>What I Learned:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Setting up a Node.js server using Express</li>
                <li>Creating dynamic HTML pages without templates</li>
                <li>Handling GET and POST requests</li>
                <li>Structuring CRUD operations</li>
                <li>Managing form inputs from the browser</li>
                <li>Understanding route parameters like :id</li>
                <li>Using Bootstrap to design fast, clean layouts</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
</body>

</html>